"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517411","Department for Education","false","2016-05-11","<p>As of March 2016, the Department for Education sources approximately 90% of its dairy products from British producers.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-05-11T16:21:00.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517411/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517411/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-04","Department for Education: Dairy Products","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of dairy products procured for her Department was sourced from British producers in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","36510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517412","Department for Education","false","2016-05-11","<p>All school admission authorities must comply with the School Admissions Code. If an admission authority identifies a fraudulent application they can withdraw the offer of a school place.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-05-11T16:22:30.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517412/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517412/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-04","Schools: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the number of parents who falsely claim religious beliefs or church attendance in order to get their children into their local school.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","36491"
