"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517416","Department for Education","false","2016-05-11","<p>The Government believes that sex and relationship education (SRE) is essential for children’s development and preparation for responsible adult life. The Secretary of State’s guidance makes clear that all schools should ensure that young people, whatever their developing sexuality or identity, feel that SRE is relevant to them and sensitive to their needs. We have received requests about updating the guidance and have made a commitment to develop an action plan for improving PSHE and have agreed to consider updating the 2000 statutory SRE guidance. In her letter of 10 February 2016 to the Education Select Committee, the Secretary of State said that she would consider updating the SRE guidance.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-05-11T16:15:06.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517416/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517416/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-04","Sex and Relationship Education: LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to update guidance for sex and relationships education so that it is inclusive of LGBT young people.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","36565"
