"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517468","Department of Health","false","2016-05-09","<p>The Department has and will continue to keep abreast of all evidence and consider it in developing policy. The report published by the Royal College of Physicians is consistent with the Government’s current policy that the best thing a smoker can do for their health is to quit smoking and quit for good but that e-cigarettes have a role to play in helping some people quit.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-05-09T14:06:27.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517468/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517468/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Electronic Cigarettes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policies of the Report, Nicotine without smoke: tobacco harm reduction, published by the Royal College of Physicians in April 2016.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","36527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517469","Department of Health","false","2016-05-11","<p>NHS Improvement, the Care Quality Commission and NHS England are working together to improve hospital standards in Essex. Three hospital trusts – Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, Mid Essex Hospital Services NHS Trust and Southend University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust – are part of the Success Regime and are working closely together with the aim of improving outcomes for patients.</p><p> </p><p>At Colchester University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, a long-term partnership has been agreed with Ipswich Hospital NHS Trust to bring about sustainable improvement for patients.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-05-11T15:34:26.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517469/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517469/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Hospitals: Essex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to improve hospital standards in Essex.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","36547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517470","Department of Health","false","2016-05-10","<p>NHS England and the Association of Directors of Adult Social Services, supported by the Department, undertook a series of visits to clinical commissioning groups and local authorities recently. These visits aimed to develop a better strategic oversight of the challenges in securing timely diagnosis across all ages and to share good practice. NHS England will report to the Cross Government Autism Programme Board in June on its findings and that report and discussion will be made public.</p><p> </p><p>As recommended by the independent Mental Health Taskforce, the Department is undertaking a five year plan for the development of mental health data to be published by the end of this year. The plan will set out future data requirements and timings for developing data to inform pathways of care which will include data requirements for autism.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","36566","2016-05-10T13:48:01.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517470/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517470/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Autism: Diagnosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to reduce waiting times for autism diagnosis.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","36563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517471","Department of Health","false","2016-05-10","<p>NHS England and the Association of Directors of Adult Social Services, supported by the Department, undertook a series of visits to clinical commissioning groups and local authorities recently. These visits aimed to develop a better strategic oversight of the challenges in securing timely diagnosis across all ages and to share good practice. NHS England will report to the Cross Government Autism Programme Board in June on its findings and that report and discussion will be made public.</p><p> </p><p>As recommended by the independent Mental Health Taskforce, the Department is undertaking a five year plan for the development of mental health data to be published by the end of this year. The plan will set out future data requirements and timings for developing data to inform pathways of care which will include data requirements for autism.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","36563","2016-05-10T13:48:01.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517471/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517471/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Autism: Diagnosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will ask NHS England to collect data on autism diagnosis waiting times.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","36566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517473","Department of Health","false","2016-05-11","<p>The number of men and boys treated in hospital for complications or after-effects arising from circumcision in a National Health Service hospital and conducted privately in each of the last three years, is not collected centrally.</p><p>The number of men and boys circumcised for medical reasons through the NHS in each of the last three years is not collected centrally. However, the table below shows a count of finished admission episodes (FAEs) where the primary procedure was a circumcision undertaken for medical reasons for boys (aged under 18 years) and men (aged 18 years and over) for 2012-13 to 2014-15.</p><p>Note that these data should not be described as counts of people as the same person may have had more than one episode of care in the time period presented.</p><p>Counts of FAEs where the primary procedure was a circumcision undertaken for medical reasons for boys (aged under 18 years) and men (aged 18 years and over) for 2012-13 to 2014-15</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Age (years)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>0-17</p></td><td><p>Over 18</p></td><td><p>Unknown</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>8,868</p></td><td><p>17,998</p></td><td><p>150</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>8,964</p></td><td><p>17,554</p></td><td><p>179</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>8,906</p></td><td><p>17,331</p></td><td><p>137</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","36600","2016-05-11T15:23:12.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517473/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517473/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Circumcision","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many men and boys were treated in hospital for complications or after-effects arising from circumcision (a) in an NHS hospital and (b) conducted privately in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","36567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517474","Department of Health","false","2016-05-09","<p>The qualitative analysis of the Local Transformation Plans will be published by NHS England as soon as possible.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-05-09T11:23:57.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517474/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517474/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 4 May 2016 to Question 35736, when he expects the qualitative analysis on key themes to become available.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","36598"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517475","Department of Health","false","2016-05-09","<p>The local transformation planning guidance was clear that clinical commissioning groups and local partners must publish their Local Transformation Plans online in an accessible format. The location where plans were published was a matter for clinical commissioning groups and their local partners.</p><p> </p><p>The Department and NHS England have compiled a list of the online links to the plans, gathered through the quarterly assurance process. The current list is based on the quarter three returns and is available on the Local Government Association website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/web/guest/health/-/journal_content/56/10180/7372943/ARTICLE" target="_blank">http://www.local.gov.uk/web/guest/health/-/journal_content/56/10180/7372943/ARTICLE</a></p><p> </p><p>Following the quarter three assurance, online links were requested from those areas where no active link had been provided.</p><p> </p><p>The expectation is that an updated list based on the quarter four position will published in the coming weeks.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-05-09T11:36:26.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517475/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517475/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 11 April 2016 to Question 32447, for what reasons some plans are not available online.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","36599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517476","Department of Health","false","2016-05-09","<p>The Government received and considered a broad range of representations from a number of stakeholders during the Spending Review process including discussions with leading nursing professionals in the Department and its arm’s length bodies.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-05-09T11:22:21.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517476/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517476/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","Health Professions: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what advice he received from senior nurses before the decision to replace NHS bursaries with student loans was announced in the Autumn Statement.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","36629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517477","Department of Health","false","2016-05-09","<p>Last year the Government introduced a series of tough financial controls to help the National Health Service tackle overspending on agency staff, including an hourly price cap. These controls include a provision for any trusts that need to override the price caps on exceptional patient safety grounds. Trusts report any such overrides on a weekly basis to NHS Improvement.</p><p> </p><p>The latest information released by NHS Improvement on the number of trusts reporting using shifts in excess of the price caps from 23 November 2015 to 7 March 2016 is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/foi-agency-shifts-exceeding-the-price-caps-by-trust" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/foi-agency-shifts-exceeding-the-price-caps-by-trust</a></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-05-09T15:54:32.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517477/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517477/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-04","NHS: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of hospital shifts breaching the national price caps for NHS agency staff occurred on patient safety grounds in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","36627"
