"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516968","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-05-11","<p>We are closely monitoring Turkish government security operations in south-east Turkey and actions it has taken in northern Iraq and northern Syria. Our condolences are with civilians caught up in the violence, as well as Turkish soldiers and police who continue to be targeted in terrorist attacks by the Kurdistan Workers’ Party (PKK). The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), and our Ambassador in Ankara have emphasised to the Turkish government the need to respect human rights, avoid civilian casualties and return to the peace process. We understand that the Government of Turkey has committed to compensating those whose properties were damaged in recent violence.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-05-11T13:16:30Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516968/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516968/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-05-03","Turkey: Armed Conflict","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of (1) whether Turkey has breached the Geneva Conventions by (a) killing and wounding unarmed civilians in south-east Turkey, and (b) firing across its frontiers with Syria and Iraq; and (2) whether there may be scope for prosecuting individuals responsible for those actions before the International Criminal Court and for claiming compensation for individuals whose property has been destroyed.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516969","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-05-11","<p>Turkey is a North Atlantic Treaty Organisation (NATO) ally and valued security partner for the UK. All countries, including NATO Allies, have a responsibility to use proportionate force when dealing with insurgents and alleged terrorists. We have no plans to call for discussion about that issue amongst NATO members.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-05-11T13:23:57.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516969/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516969/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-05-03","Turkey: NATO","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether it is their policy that the other members of NATO have a responsibility to ensure that Turkey only uses proportionate force when dealing with insurgents and alleged terrorists; and whether they intend to call for discussions about that issue amongst NATO members.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516970","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-05-11","<p>We understand that the Turkish government has proposed expropriation in order to facilitate reconstruction of certain areas damaged during security operations against the Kurdistan Workers’ Party. We have not made representations or assessed the question of collective punishment.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-05-11T13:25:09.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516970/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516970/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-05-03","Turkey: Armed Conflict","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they intend to make to the government of Turkey about the proposed expropriation and partial demolition of the Sur neighbourhood and the city of Diyarbakir; and what assessment they have made of whether those actions constitute collective punishment.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516971","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-05-10","<p>The British Government has not made representations to the Government of Saudi Arabia for full payment of arrears of wages to employees of the Saudi Bin Laden Group. We are not aware of any British nationals that have been affected.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-05-10T14:23:57.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516971/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516971/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-05-03","Saudi Arabia: Saudi Binladin Group","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they are making representations to the government of Saudi Arabia for full payment of arrears of wages to employees of the Saudi Binladin Group.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL8127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516972","Department of Health","false","2016-05-11","<p>The British Olympic Association (BOA) and British Paralympic Association (BPA) have prepared guidance to consider the health risks, including those posed by Zika, for British athletes and staff travelling to Brazil for the Olympics.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health has convened an Olympics health advisory group on behalf of the Department for Culture, Media and Sport to focus on Zika and to support the BOA and BPA to ensure that they can continue to provide the best possible information and advice.</p><p> </p><p>The group will be chaired by the Department’s Chief Scientific Advisor, Professor Chris Whitty, and will bring together experts from the BOA and BPA as well as the London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, University of Liverpool, University of Nottingham, the Royal Free London, Public Health England and across Government.</p><p> </p><p>Revisions of existing guidance or specific further advice will be published if it is deemed necessary.</p><p> </p><p>In the meantime, Public Health England and the National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) have developed and issued more general travel advice online to health professionals that is suitable for people travelling to Zika-affected countries, including pregnant women. A copy of the online advice is attached.</p><p> </p><p>This includes a list of countries where Zika virus transmission is occurring, advice around bite avoidance measures and what and who to speak to if those travelling have concerns. PHE and NaTHNaC continue to monitor the situation very closely and update advice as needed.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-05-11T16:20:48.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516972/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516972/answer","zika-virus-update-and-advice-for-travellers-including-pregnant-women.pdf","zika-virus-update-and-advice-for-travellers-including-pregnant-women.pdf","Zika Virus travel advice","Zika Virus travel advice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516972/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-03","Olympic Games: Brazil","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Lord Prior of Brampton on 11 and 12 February (HL5764 and HL5766) and by Baroness Neville-Rolfe on 11 February (HL5765), and in the light of current information about the increased extent of dangers from the Zika virus affecting up to 20 per cent of all births, whether they intend to issue further advice about, or to reconsider, in consultation with other European governments, the long-term implications of participating in or attending the 2016 Olympic Games in Brazil.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL8128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516973","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-05-11","<p>The Basic Payment Scheme (BPS), implementing the new Common Agricultural Policy, with its requirements and administrative checks, has created a number of challenges. The Rural Payments Agency focus has always been to pay as many claims as promptly as possible from the opening day of the payment window in December 2015. 99% of BPS 2015 claims have now received a payment.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-05-11T16:55:18.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516973/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516973/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-05-03","Agriculture: Subsidies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the delays by the Rural Payments Agency in making basic farm payments claimed in 2015, and of the causes of those delays.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering",,"Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","HL8129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516974","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-05-11","<p>As at 2 May, the first working day following 30 April, 98% of Basic Payment Scheme claimants had received a payment.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-05-11T13:25:49.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516974/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516974/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-05-03","Agriculture: Subsidies","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of basic farm payments claimed during 2015 had been paid as of 30 April.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering",,"Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","HL8130"
