"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516976","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-05-09","<p>A planning application for the extraction of shale gas in Ryedale is currently under consideration by North Yorkshire County Council. It would not be appropriate for the Government to comment on the specifics of any proposal. It will be for the Council to take into account the impacts of the proposed development on the local economy and the environment as relevant in its determination of that application.</p><p>The Government continues to support the development of the shale industry in the UK. It has the potential to power economic growth, create tens of thousands of jobs and provide a new domestic energy source, making us less reliant on imports from abroad.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-05-09T16:27:29.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516976/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516976/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-05-03","Fracking: Ryedale","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the possible impact on the local economy and the environment of hydraulic fracturing in Ryedale, and what were the results of the economic impact assessment carried out on that proposed development.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering",,"Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","HL8132"
