to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","36370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517071","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-09","<p>Industry rules require mobile telephone companies to provide mobile number portability (the ability to transfer a mobile phone number) to customers within the shortest possible time, and the Porting Authorisation Code (PAC) must be issued over the phone, or by text message, within two hours of a customer’s request. Companies are permitted to make reasonable charges for providing number portability, but those charges should be based on the costs of providing the PAC and should not disincentivise customers from switching. In general, mobile telephone companies do not charge customers for requesting or issuing a PAC, nor for the process of switching a customer to another provider. However, some service providers may make a termination charge, if for example a customer terminates a contract before the expiry of the minimum contract term, or if the customer changes provider before they have served out any required minimum notice period for termination (usually 30 days). The Government is committed to making it easier and quicker for consumers to switch services enabling more customers to obtain better value from their mobile service provider and fully supports Ofcom’s interim findings in the recent digital communications review. This includes Government efforts encouraging industry on a voluntary basis to remove/reduce charges for handset unlocking for consumers at the end of their contracts.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-05-09T14:53:51.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517071/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517071/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-05-03","Telecommunications: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to restrict the amount that mobile telephone companies and other communication providers can charge for the provision of a Porting Authorisation Code to customers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","36371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517073","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-09","<p>Most mobile telephone providers include terms within contracts that require customers to serve up to 30 days’ minimum notice period in order to terminate a contract, regardless of whether the customer is within the minimum term of their contract or not. Ofcom's view is that this may be longer than necessary and is currently consulting to make improvements with regards to mobile switching for consumers. In addition, the Government is committed to making it easier and quicker to switch services and fully supports Ofcom’s interim findings in the recent digital communications review.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-05-09T14:55:42.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517073/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517073/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-05-03","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to prevent mobile telephone providers from imposing long notice periods on customers who are out of contract and wish to move to another provider.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","36372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517074","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-09","<p>The Government is implementing reforms to the skills system to ensure we have the technical skills that the economy needs. We are considering when and how to publish details of our plans for further reform of the skills strategy.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-05-09T13:14:35.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517074/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517074/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-03","Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when his Department plans to publish its Skills White Paper.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517075","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-09","<p>My Rt hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills has regular discussions with the Secretary of State for Education on a wide variety of issues, including the apprenticeship levy.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-05-09T13:07:51.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517075/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517075/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-03","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Education on the liability of multi-academy trusts to pay the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517076","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-09","<p>We are working with the Cabinet Office and other government departments on helping employers in different sectors prepare for the apprenticeship levy. Only charities and voluntary organisations with a pay bill greater than £3million will pay the apprenticeship levy. These organisations and all other employers will be able to get back the funds they pay in levy if they take on apprentices. Apprenticeships can benefit all sectors, including charities, and we will work with these organisations to grow the number of apprenticeships they offer. <br></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-05-09T16:16:56.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517076/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517076/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-03","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with the Cabinet Office on the liability of charities and voluntary organisations to pay the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517078","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-09","<p>A degree apprenticeship is an approved English apprenticeship where one of the outcomes of the apprenticeship standard is a Bachelor’s or a Master’s degree awarded by the university where the apprentice undertook their academic study.</p><p> </p><p>Degree Apprenticeships policy is still under development within the existing legal framework.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-05-09T16:09:43.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517078/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517078/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-03","Apprentices: Degrees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what definition of the degree apprenticeship his Department uses in its work on that proposal.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517080","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-09","<p>The final size and structure of the Institute for Apprenticeships will be determined in due course. No decisions have yet been made about its structure or staffing.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-05-09T16:06:43.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517080/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517080/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-03","Institute for Apprenticeships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many existing staff from the Skills Funding Agency it is planned will be transferred to the new Institute for Apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517081","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>The summit will include wide-ranging discussions of ways of tackling corruption, including corporate secrecy, government transparency, the enforcement of international anti-corruption laws and the strengthening of international institutions.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:15:44.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517081/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517081/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the agenda for the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016 will include the issue of reverse burden of proof as it applies to senior managers across the financial services industry.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517082","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>The delivery of the commitments negotiated at the Anti Corruption Summit will be overseen by the Inter Ministerial Group on Corruption, which is jointly chaired by the Prime Minister's Anti-Corruption Champion and the Minister for Security in the Home Office.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:16:24.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517082/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517082/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how the Government plans to fund, monitor and report on commitments negotiated at the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517083","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-11","<p>Anguilla has now signed an arrangement to hold a central register or similarly effective system of beneficial ownership information accessible to UK tax and law enforcement agencies.</p><p>Guernsey's Chief Minister wrote to the Prime Minister on 4 April 2016 with a commitment to this too and a proposal to make a formal arrangement with the UK government when their new government is in place following their recent election.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-11T13:30:53.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517083/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517083/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Companies: Anguilla and Guernsey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether Anguilla and Guernsey have agreed to establish a central register of beneficial ownership accessible by UK tax and law enforcement agencies.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517084","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>The summit will bring together governments, international organisations, businesses and civil society to confront the problem of corruption. This includes selected representatives of the financial sector.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:15:01.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517084/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517084/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which organisations from the (a) UK and (b) international financial sector will be attending the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517086","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>The Prime Minister.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:13:47.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517086/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517086/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, who will chair the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517087","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>At the Anti Corruption Summit we will be seeking commitments on a number of measures to increase tax transparency, and reduce tax evasion and aggressive tax avoidance. The UK has called for a multilateral agreement on public country by country reporting of tax information by businesses. We welcome the recent European Commission initiative on public country by country reporting for large multinational enterprises within the EU and will work to support this.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:13:01.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517087/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517087/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he plans to seek agreement on country-by-country reporting on multinational companies at the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517089","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>Representatives of Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies have been invited to attend the Summit.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:12:07.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517089/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517089/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which of the UK's Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies will be represented at the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517091","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>We believe that it is important for governments, international organisations, civil society and businesses to work together to tackle corruption. To this end, a number of leading civil society organisations have been invited to attend the Summit. As well as the Summit itself, a pre-event on 11 May will be a important opportunity to hear a wide range of business and civil society views.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-09T13:14:26.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517091/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517091/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which civil society organisations will be attending the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","36364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517093","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-09","<p>T​he <em>'</em>Northern<em> Ireland </em>Executive<em>'</em> has committed to ​continue to deliver National Citizen Service (NCS) over the next three years​ and has appointed a provider to deliver the programme – Co-operation Ireland. ​The ​marketing and promotion of NCS in Northern Ireland will be the responsibility of Co-operation Ireland. ​</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-05-09T07:07:15.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517093/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517093/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-03","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will raise with the responsible Minister of the Northern Ireland Executive the ways in which the National Citizen Service will be promoted in Northern Ireland in the next five years immediately after the forthcoming elections to the Northern Ireland Assembly.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","36387"
